# CEO Final Sign-Off — CivicQ Landing Page

I verified the full package against the brief, the rubric, and the hard gates by
running real checks, not by trusting upstream summaries.

## What I verified (tools run, not assumed)

- **Em/en dashes:** zero matches across `cover-letter.md`, `one-pager.html`, and
  `make_deck.py` (counted the literal characters in Python; not just grep). Hard
  writing rule satisfied.
- **Deck integrity:** `deck.pptx` opens via python-pptx, 9 slides, 44 KB. Real
  file, not a stub.
- **Demo registration:** `civicq` present in `michaelwegter.com/src/data/workSamples.js`
  with correct slug, `href` (BASE_URL + demos/civicq/), and posting summary.
- **Live URLs (curl):** `/demos/civicq/` 200, `/demos/civicq/methodology.html`
  200, `api.michaelwegter.com/health` 200.
- **Live email backend:** POST `/api/civicq/subscribe` returns 201. The CSV
  export path is confirmed in deploy-test.out. The "Mailchimp/ConvertKit with CSV
  backup" requirement is proven with a working backend, not a claim.
- **Demo link presence:** appears in the one-pager (2x) and is the first line +
  body of the cover letter. Gate 4 (demo link in cover letter AND deck) holds.
- **deploy-test.out:** independent Playwright run already passed — 10 anchor
  sections reachable, 3 coded SVG visualizations rendered, methodology route live,
  end-to-end email flow to live API/SQLite confirmed. VERDICT: pass.

## Requirements coverage (brief -> package)

All explicit posting asks are addressed and represented in the demo or deck:
10 sections + sticky nav, /methodology page, dark-mode-matched system, responsive
390/1440, three custom coded visualizations (six-dimension scoring chart, $75K
funds breakdown, Org Hub wireframe), email capture + CSV backup, analytics note,
WCAG 2.1 AA, GoFundMe CTA, US-based. The four to-apply asks (portfolio, timeline,
graphics approach, fixed bid $4,200) are each answered concretely and consistently
across all three deliverables.

## Feature richness vs target (10/10)

Met. This is a full, functional build: all 10 sections as real responsive markup,
three hand-coded SVG data visualizations, a separate methodology route, and a real
email-capture-to-database backend with a live CSV export endpoint deployed to
production. Not a mockup, not a single-flow prototype.

## Voice / nonpartisan tone

Cover letter is in Michael's voice (hook, demo-as-proof, concrete build detail,
real proof points from U.S. Bank / current contract, warm low-pressure close). The
nonpartisan framing ("no spin, just the record," no red/blue color coding,
disclaimer carried through) matches the client's own positioning. No generic
filler; every client requirement is referenced concretely.

## Problems found

None that block the gate. The single 404 console line on the GH Pages SPA route is
a confirmed site-wide mechanism reproduced on an unrelated existing work-sample,
not a defect from this run.

This package wins the client: it leads with a live, working page that answers the
posting's disqualifying portfolio requirement in the first line, proves the exact
skill the job is screening for (build to spec, own the result), and prices inside
the stated range. No course-correction needed; no earlier step needs redoing.

VERDICT: pass
